1
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:19,275
'Kay. I'm all set now!
Let's head out!

2
00:00:28,442 --> 00:00:31,858
We're counting on you.
Your music's our last hope.

3
00:00:31,942 --> 00:00:33,275
--You got it!
--[SAKU, UTA] Right!

4
00:02:25,442 --> 00:02:26,567
Ushio and the others should be

5
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,733
making their moves
right now as well.

6
00:02:28,817 --> 00:02:30,192
Time for us to head inside.

7
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:31,150
[ALL]
Mm.

8
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:33,025
Yeah!

9
00:02:33,108 --> 00:02:35,442
Dude! Shut the hell up!

10
00:02:41,775 --> 00:02:43,983
Parkour!

11
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:45,358
You good, Uta?

12
00:02:45,442 --> 00:02:48,233
Yeah! No problemo!

13
00:02:48,317 --> 00:02:51,567
Cool. I'm gonna start passing
the equipment over to you.

14
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:53,900
[UTA]
Okie-dokie!

15
00:02:53,983 --> 00:02:55,525
[SOSUKE]
I'm letting it down.

16
00:02:55,608 --> 00:02:57,317
[UTA]
Gotcha!

17
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,733
[SOSUKE] Saku, hand me
the keyboard next.

18
00:02:59,817 --> 00:03:01,233
[SAKU]
Uh, right.

19
00:03:01,317 --> 00:03:05,942
'Kay. I can take it from here.
All right. Here it comes.

20
00:03:06,025 --> 00:03:07,317
[UTA]
Gimme!

21
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,358
[SOSUKE]
You got it?

22
00:03:08,442 --> 00:03:09,942
[UTA]
Yup!

23
00:03:16,775 --> 00:03:19,983
[AGENT 12A] What was that?
Hey, show yourselves, now!

24
00:03:21,983 --> 00:03:23,358
[SATSUMA]
Ryo!

25
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:27,942
[AGENT 12A]
I heard someone. Who's there?

26
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:33,525
[RYO meows]

27
00:03:33,608 --> 00:03:36,358
[AGENT 12A] And what do you
think you're doing here, kid?

28
00:03:36,442 --> 00:03:38,442
Hey. Have you by
any chance seen

29
00:03:38,525 --> 00:03:40,275
my cat somewhere
around this area?

30
00:03:40,358 --> 00:03:42,608
Your cat?

31
00:03:42,692 --> 00:03:43,733
[RYO]
Yeah, that's right.

32
00:03:43,817 --> 00:03:46,067
[MITSUKI]
Ryo. Thank you.

33
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,567
[RYO] I used to always
be able to find 'em

34
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:49,483
roaming around here
when it got out.

35
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:52,483
[SATSUMA] Ryo!
What are you doing in there!

36
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:54,358
We're not supposed to
be on school grounds!

37
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:55,983
C'mon don't you remember?

38
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,942
But what about my cat?

39
00:03:58,025 --> 00:04:00,275
[AGENT 12A] Listen, kid.
You need to leave immediately.

40
00:04:00,358 --> 00:04:03,025
For real? Leave without my cat?

41
00:04:03,108 --> 00:04:05,942
There's no way your cat could
be here, so don't argue.

42
00:04:06,025 --> 00:04:07,525
[RYO]
Huh? You sure?

43
00:04:07,608 --> 00:04:11,067
I am, so shut up and get out!
Before I really get pissed off!

44
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,733
If you stay any longer,
I'll have you arrested.

45
00:04:13,817 --> 00:04:16,817
'Kay. Guess I'll get going.

46
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,733
Well, bye.

47
00:04:25,692 --> 00:04:27,817
[ASHIHARA] What?
You expect me to climb that?

48
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,025
Quite the whining!

49
00:04:29,108 --> 00:04:31,192
We must make haste,
get up this rope, now!

50
00:04:31,275 --> 00:04:32,817
Uh...

51
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:40,733
[ASHIHARA] Do you guys think
we should really be doing this?

52
00:04:40,817 --> 00:04:42,025
[USHIO]
Well, you know what they say.

53
00:04:42,108 --> 00:04:44,983
Nothing ventured,
nothing gained!

54
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,525
[ASHIHARA scoffs]
Seriously?

55
00:04:46,608 --> 00:04:47,567
Oh, come on!

56
00:04:47,650 --> 00:04:49,400
You call yourself
a Japanese man?

57
00:04:49,483 --> 00:04:52,442
Okay, what does that
have to do with anything?

58
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:54,317
[USHIO] Once you've dedicated
yourself to something,

59
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,400
you need to see it through!

60
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,358
Hurry up! We don't have time!

61
00:05:01,442 --> 00:05:02,442
You're the only one that knows

62
00:05:02,525 --> 00:05:04,108
how to use the
broadcasting equipment!

63
00:05:04,192 --> 00:05:06,817
Cease with your useless
babbling! Get a move on!

64
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,275
This is nuts.

65
00:05:09,358 --> 00:05:11,567
[alarm blaring]

66
00:05:11,650 --> 00:05:13,608
[AGENT 12B] Thrive Central
management to security.

67
00:05:13,692 --> 00:05:15,817
We have spotted intruders
entering from the southwest

68
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,567
onto the middle school grounds.

69
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,942
All agents are to move in and

70
00:05:19,025 --> 00:05:21,608
capture the intruders
immediately! I repeat.

71
00:05:21,692 --> 00:05:23,650
We have spotted
intruders entering from...

72
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:27,650
We're about to have company.
Time for phase two.

73
00:05:27,733 --> 00:05:28,900
[SAKU, HINATA]
Mm.

74
00:05:28,983 --> 00:05:30,192
[UTA, SOSUKE]
Mm.

75
00:05:30,275 --> 00:05:33,483
[AGENT 12C] Stop!
All of you are under arrest!

76
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:38,025
This is exactly why I said
I didn't wanna do this!

77
00:05:38,108 --> 00:05:39,817
[USHIO]
Ei, Ya, Toh!

78
00:05:40,942 --> 00:05:42,733
[AGENT 12D groans]

79
00:05:42,817 --> 00:05:46,233
Fear not, knaves, I will only
use the back of my sword on you.

80
00:05:46,317 --> 00:05:49,275
But despite that mercy,
you still shall not pass!

81
00:05:49,358 --> 00:05:51,025
[KAORU gasps]
Ushio!

82
00:05:51,108 --> 00:05:53,400
Leave me! Please,
don't look back.

83
00:05:53,483 --> 00:05:55,108
[KAORU]
Mm. Come on!

84
00:05:55,192 --> 00:05:56,275
[ASHIHARA]
Huh?

85
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,358
[USHIO]
Perhaps you didn't hear me

86
00:06:00,442 --> 00:06:04,025
when I said that
you shall not pass?

87
00:06:05,275 --> 00:06:08,858
[ASHIHARA] I've changed
my mind, I wanna go home!

88
00:06:08,942 --> 00:06:10,317
[BOSS]
These Actors are obsolete,

89
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,900
so it's fine if we lose a few.
No one will miss them.

90
00:06:13,983 --> 00:06:16,692
I'm authorizing
the use of firearms.

91
00:06:16,775 --> 00:06:18,567
Make sure you clean up
this mess completely.

92
00:06:18,650 --> 00:06:19,733
[AGENT 12G]
Yes, sir!

93
00:06:20,817 --> 00:06:23,108
We're going to use the
data we gathered here

94
00:06:23,192 --> 00:06:25,150
and apply it to the
next world we create,

95
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:27,525
so it won't be a total loss.

96
00:06:27,608 --> 00:06:30,358
[KEISHI] You think that they're
just data to be harvested?

97
00:06:30,442 --> 00:06:33,025
I'll show you what
this "data" can do.

98
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:35,983
Drop your weapon!

99
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:38,858
Uh. This isn't an
honorable match -up.

100
00:06:38,942 --> 00:06:41,900
I won't say it again!
Drop your weapon, now!

101
00:06:41,983 --> 00:06:43,275
Didn't you hear me!

102
00:06:43,358 --> 00:06:44,525
[gasps]

103
00:06:45,817 --> 00:06:47,108
[USHIO]
What the--?

104
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:54,608
[AGENT 12G] Otherwise
I'll be forced to fire--

105
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,858
Drop your weapon.

106
00:07:07,358 --> 00:07:09,567
[USHIO]
I see.

107
00:07:09,650 --> 00:07:14,067
It seems that I've finally
awakened my true power!

108
00:07:15,608 --> 00:07:17,400
[USHIO giggles]

109
00:07:17,483 --> 00:07:21,025
[PLAYER 12A] Whoa, something
crazy is going on in Cat Walk!

110
00:07:21,108 --> 00:07:23,400
[PLAYER 12D]
Look at that action!

111
00:07:23,483 --> 00:07:25,025
[PLAYER 12E] Why are they
doing an event like this

112
00:07:25,108 --> 00:07:27,150
when no one can
get into the game?

113
00:07:27,233 --> 00:07:29,900
[PLAYER 12B] Someone hack around
the limited access filter!

114
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:31,858
[PLAYER 12C] What happened
with the singing contest,

115
00:07:31,942 --> 00:07:33,275
anyone know?

116
00:07:33,358 --> 00:07:35,275
[PLAYER 12F] Wait. I think
the server's back online,

117
00:07:35,358 --> 00:07:36,983
try logging in!

118
00:07:41,358 --> 00:07:44,900
[SOSUKE] Okay. We've
got power. Mic check!

119
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:51,442
[MITSUKI] Now. We just need
the outside world to notice us.

120
00:07:51,525 --> 00:07:52,483
[gasps]

121
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:54,358
[MITSUKI]
Not good.

122
00:07:54,442 --> 00:07:56,358
[MITSUKI]
Everyone! Hide!

123
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:59,108
[UTA]
Saku, follow me!

124
00:08:00,775 --> 00:08:02,692
This is no good,
we're locked out.

125
00:08:02,775 --> 00:08:05,192
So what now? I'm not
gonna be able to use

126
00:08:05,275 --> 00:08:07,733
the broadcasting
equipment from out here!

127
00:08:07,817 --> 00:08:09,650
Tell me which floor
your club room's on.

128
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:12,358
Uh. The third floor, but why?

129
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:21,733
[ASHIHARA gasps]

130
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:26,108
[ASHIHARA gasps]
Are you crazy? Hold on!

131
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:47,942
[KAORU] I'll climb up first.
And I'll pull you two up after.

132
00:08:48,025 --> 00:08:50,067
Just wait here for a second.

133
00:08:51,483 --> 00:08:52,900
'Kay?

134
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:04,608
[USUKI] How's the data
skimming on the Actors going?

135
00:09:04,692 --> 00:09:06,108
[AGENT 12I]
There's a lot to account for.

136
00:09:06,192 --> 00:09:08,650
So we only have
ten percent so far.

137
00:09:08,733 --> 00:09:09,858
That's too slow.

138
00:09:09,942 --> 00:09:11,900
Why don't you see if you
can speed things up.

139
00:09:11,983 --> 00:09:13,650
Yes, sir.

140
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:15,650
[AGENT 12J] Excuse me,
do you have a moment, sir?

141
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:16,900
[USUKI]
Hm?

142
00:09:16,983 --> 00:09:18,608
[STUDENTS shouting]

143
00:09:18,692 --> 00:09:20,733
[TAKATO] How long do you
plan on keeping us locked out?

144
00:09:20,817 --> 00:09:22,525
Open the gates!

145
00:09:22,608 --> 00:09:25,233
We have a right to get into
our own school grounds!

146
00:09:25,317 --> 00:09:28,150
The government can't keep us
out of our dorms forever!

147
00:09:28,233 --> 00:09:33,317
Silence! Get away from here!
Disperse immediately!

148
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:37,692
Quit trying to tell us
what to do, you bastard!

149
00:09:37,775 --> 00:09:39,608
Open these gates, right now!

150
00:09:39,692 --> 00:09:44,817
[STUDENTS]
Open up! Open up! Open up!

151
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,858
What is going on out there?

152
00:09:46,942 --> 00:09:48,567
Sir, it would seem

153
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:52,192
the students have gathered in
a crowd near the front gates.

154
00:09:52,275 --> 00:09:54,317
And those barricaded in
the broadcast room?

155
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,942
Still at large.
We can't flush them out.

156
00:09:57,025 --> 00:09:59,858
Good. The players are
starting to log back on.

157
00:09:59,942 --> 00:10:01,775
Now it's time to
let them all loose.

158
00:10:01,858 --> 00:10:03,275
[BOSS]
What do you think you're doing?

159
00:10:03,358 --> 00:10:04,525
[gasps]

160
00:10:04,608 --> 00:10:05,733
[AGENT 12L] Sir, we're
getting bug reports from

161
00:10:05,817 --> 00:10:07,858
players who've gained
unauthorized access!

162
00:10:07,942 --> 00:10:09,317
I don't want them interfering,

163
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,108
cut off all electrical power
to Thrive Central, now!

164
00:10:12,192 --> 00:10:14,858
[AGENT 12L]
Are you sure about that, sir?

165
00:10:14,942 --> 00:10:18,525
[KEISHI] That would
be unwise. Come now.

166
00:10:18,608 --> 00:10:21,858
You'd be wasting all that money
and development time you spent!

167
00:10:21,942 --> 00:10:23,733
You'll have to make your
new Actors from scratch

168
00:10:23,817 --> 00:10:25,150
if you do that.

169
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:28,858
Mr. Harumoto. You really
shouldn't eavesdrop like that,

170
00:10:28,942 --> 00:10:30,483
it's rather unbecoming.

171
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:33,983
Wow, you have some nerve
saying that to me, "Boss."

172
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:36,608
After all, I'm supposed to be
Thrive Central's manager,

173
00:10:36,692 --> 00:10:38,983
but you cut me off
without any warning.

174
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:40,692
It had already been decided that

175
00:10:40,775 --> 00:10:43,275
Thrive Central was
to be shut down.

176
00:10:43,358 --> 00:10:45,150
We knew you wouldn't
accept that decision,

177
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,025
so there was no point
in telling you.

178
00:10:47,108 --> 00:10:48,733
You'd do something foolish.

179
00:10:48,817 --> 00:10:51,983
You've got me pegged!
Anyway, if that's the truth,

180
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:54,483
you must be backing up all
the data you can right now,

181
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:56,150
is that correct?

182
00:10:56,233 --> 00:10:58,650
I don't see how that's
any of your business.

183
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:01,400
Oh my, why do you seem
so flustered, sir?

184
00:11:01,483 --> 00:11:03,317
Is there something that you
don't want the higher-ups

185
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:06,900
to know about Thrive Central's
main system and operations?

186
00:11:06,983 --> 00:11:09,150
That's utterly preposterous.

187
00:11:09,233 --> 00:11:11,317
Now do me a favor and
stay in your room--

188
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,525
though, not like you
have any choice.

189
00:11:19,358 --> 00:11:21,275
So do you boys want to
tell me what it is

190
00:11:21,358 --> 00:11:23,275
you think you can
accomplish here?

191
00:11:23,358 --> 00:11:26,775
We could ask you the same.
Do you care to explain yourself?

192
00:11:26,858 --> 00:11:29,775
This world is going to
meet its end very soon.

193
00:11:29,858 --> 00:11:32,067
You lot can't be
saved as you are.

194
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:35,817
But if we back up your data, we
can make better versions of you.

195
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,067
What are you talking about?

196
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:39,108
This doesn't make any sense.

197
00:11:39,192 --> 00:11:41,108
[USUKI] It's a waste of
time trying to fill you in

198
00:11:41,192 --> 00:11:42,567
on all the details.

199
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:45,233
In any event,
you're coming with me.

200
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,650
[gasps]

201
00:11:50,692 --> 00:11:52,608
Is that my cat? But how?

202
00:11:52,692 --> 00:11:53,567
[USUKI]
You little!

203
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:54,817
[gasps]

204
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,525
[ALL gasp]

205
00:12:04,525 --> 00:12:06,233
[AGENT 12N]
Are you all right, sir?

206
00:12:08,817 --> 00:12:11,650
[gasps] What are you--?

207
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:15,400
You goons have got some nerve
using me as your puppet!

208
00:12:15,483 --> 00:12:16,817
Mr. Usuki!

209
00:12:20,692 --> 00:12:23,775
[USHIO yelling]

210
00:12:27,108 --> 00:12:31,233
Take that, ne'er-do-well!
Taste my steel!

211
00:12:41,358 --> 00:12:42,775
It's Chiguma!

212
00:12:45,858 --> 00:12:48,233
Hey, boys. Sorry we're late.

213
00:12:48,317 --> 00:12:50,775
[HINATA]
Mike's here, too!

214
00:12:50,858 --> 00:12:53,025
Didja miss me?

215
00:12:53,108 --> 00:12:54,525
Thank goodness!

216
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:57,650
Mitsuki! You guys have
an audience waiting!

217
00:12:57,733 --> 00:13:00,067
Show them what you all can do!

218
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:02,567
Wait. Keishi?

219
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:04,192
[chuckles]

220
00:13:04,275 --> 00:13:07,317
[AGENT 12Q]
Open up! Get out here right now!

221
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,692
That's an order!

222
00:13:09,775 --> 00:13:14,983
{\an8}What're you guys waiting for?
C'mon, hurry up and start!

223
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:19,567
{\an8}[STUDENTS]
Open up! Open up! Open up!

224
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:20,483
[booming]

225
00:13:20,567 --> 00:13:22,442
[ALL]
Huh?

226
00:13:22,525 --> 00:13:24,358
[STUDENT 12A]
Wait, what is going on?

227
00:13:24,442 --> 00:13:26,900
[STUDENTS chattering]

228
00:13:26,983 --> 00:13:31,150
[MITSUKI] And now we shall begin
the Tensho School's annual

229
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,942
Autumn Festival
Singing Competition!

230
00:13:33,025 --> 00:13:34,567
They're on the loudspeakers?

231
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:36,733
Heck yeah!

232
00:13:36,817 --> 00:13:37,567
[music playing]

233
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,858
All right!

234
00:13:38,942 --> 00:13:40,567
[STUDENT 12B]
It's Sakutasuke!

235
00:13:40,650 --> 00:13:41,567
[GIN]
Seriously?

236
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:43,067
[TAMOTSU]
Way to go, Mitsuki!

237
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:44,608
[SATORU]
All right!

238
00:13:47,275 --> 00:13:53,317
♪ From the loneliness
blossoms a flower of hope ♪

239
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:56,650
♪ The wind blowing
fiercely and strong ♪

240
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,400
♪ Stand up straight and tall ♪

241
00:13:58,483 --> 00:14:02,442
♪ So you're not pulled along ♪

242
00:14:02,525 --> 00:14:04,692
♪ As the world sways ♪

243
00:14:04,775 --> 00:14:06,525
[STUDENT 12D gasps]
What was that?

244
00:14:06,608 --> 00:14:08,108
[CATS meowing]

245
